It enables you to build distributed and scalable applications by allowing the decoupling of the components in a microservices architecture.
SNS supports the publish-subscribe messaging paradigm, where publishers send messages to topics, and subscribers receive those messages.
U can send messages and notifs with sns .
*Topics :
A topic is an access point for allowing communication between publishers and subscribers. Publishers send messages to topics,
and subscribers receive messages from topics.
Multiple subscribers can subscribe to a single topic, and a single message can be delivered to multiple subscribers.
